# HealthLens AI — Implementation Plan

An intelligent preventive healthcare platform that predicts disease risk, tracks health trends over time, and simulates lifestyle interventions using Groq LLM + ML-style logic, all wrapped in a premium Awwwards-level UI.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Groq API Key needed**: The AI features (risk prediction, explainable AI, lifestyle simulation, doctor summary) all use the **Groq API** (free tier). Please provide your Groq API key so I can add it to [.env](file:///c:/Users/diksh/OneDrive/Desktop/healthlens-ai/backend/.env). Get one free at https://console.groq.com — it's instant.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Tech Stack**: This uses **React + Vite** for the frontend (in `healthlens-ai/frontend/`) and the existing **Node.js/Express** backend. The current backend server running on port 5000 will need to be restarted after changes.

> [!NOTE]
> **No Python ML needed**: Instead of setting up a separate Python ML server (complex), I'll use **Groq LLM (llama3-8b)** on the backend to intelligently analyze biomarker data and generate risk scores, explanations, and simulations. This is actually MORE impressive than traditional sklearn models for a portfolio — and Groq is extremely fast (< 1 second latency).

